xubamp (0.1.2-1) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Visualization refresh slider uses the classic fps scale (10 fps up
    to ~70 fps) and shows the resulting fps in Preferences; falloff
    sliders read slow-to-fast.
  * XUBAMP_DEBUG_FPS=1 prints the achieved visualizer frame rate for
    diagnostics.
  * Stale development branch removed; main carries every release.

 -- Hector Oviedo <hector.ernesto.oviedo@gmail.com>  Wed, 16 Jul 2026 18:00:00 +0000

xubamp (0.1.1-1) resolute; urgency=medium

  * The playlist persists across close and reopen (session.m3u8 plus the
    remembered current row); reopening never autoplays.
  * Visualization pacing fixed: the analyzer/scope is timer-paced at the
    chosen refresh rate instead of stalling on throttled compositor
    frame callbacks.
  * Mouse wheel adjusts volume anywhere on the main window, pans over
    the balance slider, and seeks over the position bar.
  * The playlist scrollbar uses the skin's classic handle sprite.
  * Right-clicking a playlist row pops a per-track menu (Play, File
    Info, Remove Selected, Crop).
  * Shuffle Previous with no history jumps to a random track, like the
    original.
  * A stopped deck shows a blank clock instead of 0:00; popup menus
    open without a pre-highlighted row.

 -- Hector Oviedo <hector.ernesto.oviedo@gmail.com>  Wed, 16 Jul 2026 16:00:00 +0000

xubamp (0.1.0-1) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Tag-aware display: ID3v2/Vorbis/RIFF tags feed the classic
    "N. Artist - Title (M:SS)" marquee and the playlist rows.
  * Play/pause/stop indicator with the classic paused blink; the
    windowshade strip gains the song title and transport feedback.
  * Playlist: live current-track clock, per-track durations, working
    bottom clusters, Audio Library scans.
  * Double-size mode (Ctrl+D), an interactive clutterbar, and a file
    info box with an editable ID3v1 tag form.
  * Preferences: Options, full Visualization, Display, and a working
    Audio Library page; options act on the live player.
  * Windows drag from any free surface; a quick click-then-drag no
    longer toggles windowshade instead of dragging.
  * New hotkeys: R, S, L, Ctrl+D, Alt+3.

 -- Hector Oviedo <hector.ernesto.oviedo@gmail.com>  Wed, 16 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0000

